other written law or that any of the conditions of the licence 
has not been complied with;

(c)  where it is satisfied that the motor vehicle has been or is intended 
to be used for an unlawful purpose or that the original purpose 
for which the licence was issued no longer exists:

(a)  the type and extent of intermediation business to be operated 
or  provided  by  the  holder  of  an  intermediation  business 
licence;

(b)  the general level of service to be provided to persons using 
services provided by the holder of an intermediation business 
licence;

(a)  if any of the provisions of this Act or any of the conditions of 
the  intermediation  business  licence  has  not  been  complied 
with;

(f)  to  the  use  of  a  motor  vehicle  for  the  purpose  of  the 
Government or local authority when such  vehicle is owned 
by the Government or local authority;

the maximum permissible laden weight of the vehicle 
does not exceed such weight as the Board may specify 
from time to time;

(b)  any financial interest whatsoever which he has in the business 
of any other person or company which provides facilities for 
the transport of passengers or goods within Malaysia;

(b)  makes or has in his possession any mark, plate or document 
so closely resembling any such  mark, plate or document as 
aforesaid as to be calculated to deceive;

(c)  alters  any  entry  made  in  a  register,  licence,  intermediation 
business licence or other document issued or kept under this 
Act;

(e)  exhibits on any motor vehicle any licence or intermediation 
business  licence  or  identification  mark,  plate  or  document 
which does not belong to such vehicle;

(d)  that  any  person  is  not  the  holder  of  a  licence  or  an 
intermediation  business  licence  issued  under  this  Act  in 
respect of a motor vehicle;

(e)  that  any  person  is  not  the  holder  of  a  licence  or  an 
intermediation  business  licence  authorizing  him  to  provide 
any particular service;

(a)  without reasonable excuse, proof of which shall lie on him, 
